[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi all, I'm beginner of Lean. The question is extremely silly but I've been stuck on it for almost an hour. <strong>So I have real numbers a, b, c with c &gt; 0, and I already proved a &lt; b / c. Now I just want to conclude that c * a &lt; b.</strong> But I simply cannot find a theorem for it. I've tried all sorts of <code>XX_lt_div_XX</code> and none applies. Can anyone point me to a correct way?</p>",
        "id": 523791687,
        "sender_full_name": "Hampy Chan",
        "timestamp": 1749745165
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please post your question as a code with <code>sorry</code> in the place you don't know how to continue.<br>\nAlso reading <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a> might be helpful.</p>",
        "id": 523792003,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1749745296
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks. Below is the mwe:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cpos</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 523792734,
        "sender_full_name": "Hampy Chan",
        "timestamp": 1749745584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is not a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a> because the imports are not there, so your file does not compile.<br>\nOnce you have a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a>, hopefully <code>exact?</code> should tell you exactly the lemma you need.</p>",
        "id": 523792885,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1749745627
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just wrote <code>hint</code> and it gave me a proof:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">lt_div_iff₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cpos</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 523792943,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1749745645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can for instance do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cpos</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and look at the output of <code>exact?</code>.</p>",
        "id": 523793090,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1749745691
    },
